This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with language modeling using recurrent neural networks. It could also belong to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it proposes a new architecture for neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) as it deals with natural language processing. "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) is another possible category as it deals with neural networks. Finally, "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with image or video data, but it could be relevant if the proposed architecture is applied to visual data.
